ActIndian Act
SubjectPeguis Indian Band CLAIM SETTLEMENT AGREEMENT
PrecisAuthority to (a) enter into a specific claim SETTLEMENT AGREEMENT with the PEGUIS INDIAN BAND for the purpose of compensating the Band for its specific claim with respect to the unlawful 1907 surrrender of the St. Peter's Reserve in the Province of Manitoba, and (b) accept the Instrument of Absolute Surrender of the lands described in Article 3 of the settlement agreement.
